HEADWORD: Punctuative
<hw>Punc"tu*a*tive</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Of or belonging
to points of division; relating to punctuation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>punctuative</qex> intonation of feeble cadence.</q>
